main event: A civilian reported observing a pure hazy white solid object in the sky near Sloan, Nevada on 20 March 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for approximately 20 seconds,The object was described as solid-looking with no observable structure,The weather conditions were clear during the sighting,The camera used to capture the image had a slow shutter speed, leading to potential issues in capturing detail,Investigation into the photo analysis revealed inconsistencies, suggesting no clear evidence of a solid object.
sighted object: a pure hazy white solid object
witness description: A civilian who saw the object while driving on U.S. Highway 91
